Raspberry Oatmeal Bars    gf
  --Bob's Red Mill
  
1/2 c (1 stick) unsalted butter, melted
2 tsp vanilla, divided
1 c gf oat flour
1 c gf rolled oats
1/2 c sugar
1 1/2 tsp xanthan gum
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp grated lemon zest
1/2 tsp sea salt
2/3 c raspberry jam or preserves

Preheat oven to 375F; generously grease 8x8" pan. In medium bowl, combine butter amd 1 tsp vanilla. Stir in flour, oats, sugar, xanthan gum, baking powder, zest, and salt until thoroughly blended. Press 1 c of mixture firmly into bottom of prepared pan. Stir remaining tsp of vanilla into raspberry jam until smooth, then spread evenly on top. Sprinkle remaining oat mixture over jam, then press firmly to make top layer smooth and even. Bake 20-25 min or until top is lightly browned and firm. Cool bars in pan for 30 min on wire rack. Cut into 16 squares and serve at room temp.
